4.1 Primary Memory (Main Memory)
Directly accessible by CPU
Volatile (data lost on power off)

a) RAM (Random Access Memory)
SRAM
Faster, expensive
Used in cache
DRAM
Slower, cheaper
Used as main memory

b) ROM (Read Only Memory)
Non-volatile
Stores firmware (BIOS/UEFI)
Types: PROM, EPROM, EEPROM, Flash

4.2 Secondary Memory
Non-volatile
Large storage capacity
Slower access
Examples: SSD, HDD
